  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Equation.}\n\\[\n\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0802}}:\\mathcal{X}_{\\mathrm{id0802}}\\longrightarrow \\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{id0802}},\\qquad\n\\mathcal{N}_{\\mathrm{TRAWIN}}(\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0802}})=\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0802}},\\qquad\n\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0802}}(x)\\in\\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{adm}}.\n\\]\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.} The carrier of the entry is the id-specific bundle map.  Define\\[\n\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0802}}:\\mathcal{X}_{\\mathrm{id0802}}\\longrightarrow \\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{id0802}}.\n\\]\n\nThe TRAWIN normalization acts as an internal compatibility projector:\\[\n\\mathcal{N}_{\\mathrm{TRAWIN}}(\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0802}})=\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0802}}.\n\\]\n\nTopological closure is obtained by requiring every admissible input to land inside the allowed target class:\\[\n\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0802}}(x)\\in\\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{adm}}.\n\\]\n\nThus the Nonary derivation for [ID 0802] is the three-stage passage\n\\[\n\\mathcal{X}_{\\mathrm{id0802}}\\xrightarrow{\\,\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0802}}\\,} \\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{id0802}}\\xrightarrow{\\,\\mathcal{N}_{\\mathrm{TRAWIN}}\\,} \\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{adm}},\n\\]\nwith the entry title fixing the meaning of the carrier and the TRAWIN normalization fixing the admissibility test.\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.} SO(3) times U(1) Configuration Bundle is therefore treated as a stable carrier: it can transport the Nonary state only when its bundle map is normalized and its output remains inside the admissible target geometry.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
